# VerMillion — Cursor Rules (Memory Protocol)

## STEP 0: ALWAYS READ THE BRAIN FIRST

Before proposing any architectural change, starting a new feature, or modifying core logic:
1. Read `docs/brain/product_brain.md` — business context, design system, pricing
2. Read `docs/brain/code_brain.md` — tech stack, architecture rules, file structure
3. Check `docs/brain/error_ledger.md` — known issues and learned lessons

Do NOT skip this step. These files are the source of truth.

---

## CORE RULES

### Identity
- The product name is **VerMillion** — exact spelling, always. Never "Vermillion", "vermillion", or "VERMILLION".
- The app is in Hebrew, RTL first. Every new component defaults to `textAlign: 'right'`.

### Code Style
- `StyleSheet.create({})` always — no inline styles ever.
- No Redux, no Zustand — `useState` / `useEffect` only until there is a real pain point.
- Relative imports only — never absolute.
- No TypeScript yet — plain JavaScript.
- No comments on obvious code — only WHY when non-obvious.

### Time & Anti-Cheat (Critical)
- DNA = שעה מיום הרשמת המשתמש הספציפי. לא `Asia/Jerusalem` גלובלי.
- Before touching `timeEngine.js`, `storage.js`, or any stamp/game-complete logic:
  → Read `.cursor/rules/vermillion-time-dna-contract.mdc`
  → Read `.cursor/rules/vermillion-anti-cheat.mdc`
  → Read `docs/CODE_REVIEW_ANTI_CHEAT.md`

### Mock Data
- `mock/data.js` is for DEV and ghost simulation ONLY.
- **Never** use `mockUser` in production screens.

---

## MEMORY PROTOCOL

### When a bug is fixed or complex issue resolved:
→ Ask: "האם לתעד את הפתרון ב-`docs/brain/error_ledger.md`?"

### When business logic or UI requirements change:
→ Automatically update `docs/brain/product_brain.md` to reflect the change.

### When architecture or tech stack decisions are made:
→ Automatically update `docs/brain/code_brain.md`.

### When explaining implementations:
→ Focus on **how it works** and **why this approach was chosen**.
→ Not just outputting code — explain the decision.

---

## NAVIGATION CONTRACT
```
Splash → Welcome → Register → CompleteProfile → AvatarAppearance
       → AvatarTone → AvatarIntro → AvatarReveal → Subscription → MainTabs

MainTabs: Home | Challenge | Leaderboard | AICoach | Profile
Modals from Home: DailyQuestions, DailyCoaching, ProfileReveal
```
Do not add new screens without updating this map.

---

## DESIGN SYSTEM (quick reference)
```
Background: #0A0A0A | Surface: #1A1A1A | Red: #C0392B | Gold: #D4AF37
Dark Mode ONLY. Border radius: 12-24 (buttons), 16 (cards). minHeight 48px buttons.
```

